output_data.summary: Follow-up session addressing the worsening severity of depressive symptoms and evaluating the efficacy of current pharmacotherapy.
output_data.reasoning: The patient presented with classic symptoms of a Major Depressive Episode (anhedonia, terminal insomnia, significant fatigue, weight loss, and reported passive death ideation). The session focus was clinical management, specifically increasing the Sertraline dose from 50mg to 100mg daily following an inadequate response over four weeks, and ruling out any history of hypomania/mania.
